node.title: Star All Whites defender Cacace joins Italian Serie A side Empoli on loan
node.description: The 21-year-old is set to become the first Kiwi to play in Italy's famed Serie A.
node.content: ["All Whites defender Liberato Cacace is poised to become the first New Zealander to play in Italy's Serie A, after joining Empoli on loan.", "Cacace, 21, will link with the Italian team from his Belgian club Sint-Truiden, where he's made 46 appearances since he signed a three-year contract in 2020.", "At the end of the Serie A season, there's an option for Empoli to make the loan deal permanent.", "The Florence-based team currently sit 12th on the Serie A ladder, with just over half of the season completed.", "After representing New Zealand at age-group level, the left back stamped his mark with Wellington Phoenix in 2018, becoming one of the A-League's premier defenders at just 18 years old.", "Born to an Italian father and Kiwi mother of Italian descent, Cacace went on to make his All Whites debut in 2018 and has since earned five international caps.", "He also starred for the NZ U-23 side at last year's Tokyo Olympics.", "\u00a0"]
